  "texts": [
    "The ensemble provides confidence regions on any desired quantity, which can be easily extracted by marginalization.",
    "Conceptually, lens-model ensembles are like Monte-Carlo Markov chains widely used for likelihood or posterior-probability sampling.",
    "Model ensembles may contain extreme models, but that does not mean the posterior p(| D) is uniform in all properties between the extremes.",
    "To give an analogy, consider an ensemble of random walks with a given number and length of steps, and no preference between different random walks.",
    "The ensemble will span every random walk from zero net displacement to a straight line (i.e., the maximum displacement possible), but the distribution of displacements will not be uniform between these extremes."
